	Open command prompt and start: 
  
  Installation
	
	1. Check for node installation:       
     node -v
	   if it is unrecognized command then download node from www.nodejs.org and install the latest version
	
  2. Check for angular cli installation:  
     ng -v
	   if it is unrecognized command then: 
     npm install -g @angular/cli
	
	Basic app

	1. To create it from cmd: 
     ng new <new-project-name>
	2. To enter to the project: 
     cd <new-project-name>
	3. Install typescript: 
     npm install typescript  --save 
	4. To launch the app: 
     ng-serve
  5. Open in browser to check out:  http://localhost:4200
